{
  "doc_id": "34374",
  "text": "Although several studies have indicated that bladder cancer is a common disease associated with substantial economic burden for patients and society, the evidence of cost-effectiveness of bladder cancer interventions is limited and of insufficient quality [CITATION_1] . In this article, we review several bladder cancer interventions that have been established as cost-effective and should be, but are generally not, adopted for wider use.",
